cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new coding scheme using non-binary LDPC codes and discusses its rate compatibility and performance. This falls under the scope of information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper proposes a decoding algorithm for the proposed codes and discusses its computational complexity. This falls under the scope of computational complexity. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The proposed codes can be used in communication systems and networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed codes can be used in control systems and signal processing, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the construction of rate-compatible codes using multiplicatively repeated non-binary LDPC codes, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
